---
import Layout from '../../layouts/main.astro';
---

<Layout title="Markdown Test - Development Only">
  <article class="container mx-auto py-12 px-4 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="mb-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-primary">Markdown Test Page</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground">
        Development page - Testing markdown rendering and typography
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-300 dark:border-yellow-700 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800 dark:text-yellow-200">
          ⚠️ This page is available only in development mode
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>About Markdown</h2>
      <p>
        This page demonstrates how Markdown content is rendered with our custom PIU theme.
        It includes various elements to test typography and styling.
      </p>
      
      <h3>Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Clean typography with optimal readability</li>
        <li>Consistent spacing and hierarchy</li>
        <li>Dark mode support</li>
        <li>Mobile-responsive design</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Code Example</h3>
      <pre><code>const message = 'Hello PIU dApp!';
console.log(message);</code></pre>

      <blockquote>
        <p>This is a blockquote example to showcase the quote styling in our design system.</p>
      </blockquote>

      <h3>Links and Emphasis</h3>
      <p>
        You can use <strong>bold text</strong>, <em>italic text</em>, and 
        <a href="#" class="text-primary hover:underline">links</a> throughout your content.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
